subSubSection.paragraph:
Male abdomen: subgenital plate tapered, apically narrowly truncate in ventral or dorsal view (
Fig. 14A
). Genitalia (
Figs 14D–F
) with parapennis pointed apically and its medial edge straight; harpe longer than wide, wider than apex of basiparamere, with medial edge distinctly convex at basal third and distinctly concave near base, lateral edge gently rounded, and apex narrowly rounded. Penis valve with paravalva large and expanded, ventrally with distinct spinules (
Figs 14F, K, L
); valvispina directed posteroventrally.

Distribution . Japan : Hokkaido , Honshu, Shikoku, Kyushu (
Shinohara et al . 2000
).
